Hey guys! Rick here to explain the meme The joke here is to do with this security code that seems to be slightly unintelligent. Basically, the code as seen has three keys that stand out, which is due to continues use by people. These three keys are 3, 9, and 4. Whats unintelligent is that there is a worryingly strong chance that the numbers above it which represents the number of the house/flat, is in fact the correct code. There are 12 possible answers with these three different keys however I believe that someone has been dumb enough to make their code, the number that’s directly above it. The image below mocks this person by misspelling the word ‘security’ as this person may as well not even have a door, let alone a keypad due to how not secured this home is.
